CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 21, 1945, pg. 15 reads: "Bride And Groom - A pair of happy newlyweds, Corp. and Mrs. Carl Morris, were snapped just about to cut the wedding cake last Thursday at their reception at the home of the bride's father on Wylie Avenue. The lovely bride is the former Eloise Mosby.  The groom is stationed at Tampa, Fla. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Groom Carl Morris wearing military uniform, and bride Eloise Mosby, standing behind three tiered wedding cake in interior with floral trimmed curtains
